#: ../../source/vuln/ssti.rst:58
msgid "``__class__``"
msgstr "``__class__``"

#: ../../source/vuln/ssti.rst:59
msgid ""
"python中的新式类（即显示继承object对象的类）都有一个属性 ``__class__`` 用于获取当前实例对应的类，例如 "
"``\"\".__class__`` 就可以获取到字符串实例对应的类"
msgstr "New-style classes in Python, meaning classes that explicitly inherit from ``object``, have an attribute named ``__class__`` that obtains the class corresponding to the current instance. For example, ``\"\".__class__`` obtains the class corresponding to a string instance."

#: ../../source/vuln/ssti.rst:62
msgid "``__mro__``"
msgstr "``__mro__``"

#: ../../source/vuln/ssti.rst:63
msgid ""
"python中类对象的 ``__mro__`` "
"属性会返回一个tuple对象，其中包含了当前类对象所有继承的基类，tuple中元素的顺序是MRO（Method Resolution Order）"
" 寻找的顺序。"
msgstr "In Python, the ``__mro__`` attribute of a class object returns a tuple containing all base classes inherited by the current class object. The order of elements in the tuple is the lookup order used by MRO (Method Resolution Order)."

#: ../../source/vuln/ssti.rst:66
msgid "``__globals__``"
msgstr "``__globals__``"

#: ../../source/vuln/ssti.rst:67
msgid ""
"保存了函数所有的所有全局变量，在利用中，可以使用 ``__init__`` 获取对象的函数，并通过 ``__globals__`` 获取 "
"``file`` ``os`` 等模块以进行下一步的利用"
msgstr "This stores all global variables of a function. During exploitation, ``__init__`` can be used to obtain an object's function, and ``__globals__`` can then be used to obtain modules such as ``file`` and ``os`` for the next exploitation step."

#: ../../source/vuln/ssti.rst:70
msgid "``__subclasses__()``"
msgstr "``__subclasses__()``"

#: ../../source/vuln/ssti.rst:71
msgid ""
"python的新式类都保留了它所有的子类的引用，``__subclasses__()`` "
"这个方法返回了类的所有存活的子类的引用（是类对象引用，不是实例）。"
msgstr "Python new-style classes keep references to all of their subclasses. The ``__subclasses__()`` method returns references to all live subclasses of a class; these are class object references, not instances."

#: ../../source/vuln/ssti.rst:73
msgid ""
"因为python中的类都是继承object的，所以只要调用object类对象的 ``__subclasses__()`` "
"方法就可以获取想要的类的对象。"
msgstr "Because classes in Python inherit from ``object``, calling the ``__subclasses__()`` method on the ``object`` class object can be used to obtain the desired class object."

